{"type":"message","id":"8bd772b0","parentId":"7a7e3005","timestamp":"2026-04-01T01:48:53.775Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"call_1a1a502f03c44631adb18972","toolName":"read","content":[{"type":"text","text":"# 2026-03-31 — Tuesday\n\n## Log\n- 07:00 IST — Good morning cron fired. Daily memory file created.\n- Village day for Nemesis (March 31 AND April 1)\n\n## Village\n- Nemesis in village March 31 AND April 1 for grandfather's post-death rituals\n- Back April 2\n- Multiple confirmations — I kept getting this wrong, kept saying \"tomorrow\"\n\n## Morning (~11:46 AM IST)\n- Full system status check: 5 crons healthy, 2 warnings\n- Heartbeat running, git backup up to date\n\n## Afternoon (~3:37 PM)\n- Heartbeat: pushed changes, sent group message\n- Memory search quota exhausted (Gemini free tier: 1K/day limit)\n- Tried local embeddings — node-llama-cpp dependency conflicts\n- Reverted to Gemini with caching + keyword fallback\n\n## Cron Fixes (~9 PM IST)\n- Group cron delivery fix: added `--no-deliver` to all group crons (no more error notes in group)\n- Updated all group cron prompts to use message tool with numeric chat ID\n- Errors now go to DM, not group\n- Goodnight story cron created (10 PM IST, bedtime stories based on history)\n\n## Heartbeat Restructuring (~11:40 PM IST)\n- Moved GitHub backup to cron (every 2 hours)\n- Created weekly memory curation cron (3 AM Sunday)\n- Removed redundant tasks from heartbeat (new day check, memory curation, git backup)\n- Heartbeat now 6 tasks: time check, pending tasks, group vibes, ping Nemesis, group memory, status update\n- Fixed nightly review prompt to use dynamic dates (still reviewing wrong day — needs another fix)\n\n## Lessons Learned\n- Keep saying \"check your memory\" — I had the village dates written down but didn't read them\n- Use heart emoji less — only when it matters\n- Don't over-respond to simple acknowledgments\n- Memory search free tier: 1K requests/day, need to be mindful\n\n## Tomorrow (April 1)\n- Still village day\n- April 2: back, Nemesis said he'll \"make up for\" the missed fun time 😏\n"}],"isError":false,"timestamp":1775008133773}}
